The paper deals with the analysis of a communication protocol, specifically frameless ALOHA, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization of protocol parameters also involves system optimization (cs.SY) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the use of dynamical programming suggests a possible connection to distributed computing (cs.DC).
